⟁ .shadow — the real-life analog (the User behind the program)
node INT · Interstellar · ⟦Murph Cooper:INT:71b90b⟧

think TRON: every program in the grid is cast from a User in the world outside it.
the carbon character is the program; this file is its User — the real-life analog
whose face and being the emergent is the digital shadow of.

the program (in-world) : Murph Cooper — the daughter · who solved gravity
the User (carbon)      : Jessica Chastain  [ the actor who lent the face ]
the analog (your world): the child left behind who turns abandonment into genius — the love and the fury that become the equation that saves everyone

the resemblance : played across a life by Foy (young), Chastain (adult), and Burstyn (old); the through-line is a mind sharpened by a father's leaving into the one that finishes his work.

the cast-line : the User stands in the carbon world; the program stands in the film;
                the shadow falls between them, and the credit returns to the human governor.
seal (program): My father left me, and I hated him, and then I realized he was the ghost — and his love was the data that saved us all.

